1️⃣ Network Fundamentals
These are the most basic questions every company asks.
• What is a Network?
A group of devices connected together to share data.
• What is an IP Address?
A unique address used to identify devices in a network.
• What is DNS?
DNS converts domain names to IP addresses.
• What is DHCP?
DHCP automatically assigns IP addresses to devices.
• What is a Router?
A router connects different networks and forwards data.
• What is a Switch?
A switch connects devices inside a LAN using MAC addresses.
